{"id":1260,"date":"2010-12-08T06:33:26","date_gmt":"2010-12-08T12:33:26","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/a_refined_divx.php"},"modified":"2010-12-08T06:33:26","modified_gmt":"2010-12-08T12:33:26","slug":"a_refined_divx","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/a_refined_divx.php","title":{"rendered":"A Refined DivX"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/divx_logo.gif\" alt=\"DivX Logo, Before and After\"><\/p>\n<p>Manned by 350 employees through offices in seven countries, <a href=\"http:\/\/www.divx.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">DivX Inc<\/a> produces its eponymous technology that enable the conversion, distribution and consumption of high-quality video and media experiences across mobile devices, computers, televisions, and other devices. Even if you are not fully aware of it, you might have a DVD player or TV that can play back DivX encoded media. Around October, DivX introduced a new identity.<\/p><!--more--><blockquote>You may have seen a few changes on divx.com and noticed that the world has become a more beautiful place. You didn&#8217;t? Oh. Well, we recently unveiled a new DivX logo, new style and a simplified website &mdash; and even if you don&#8217;t stay awake at night studying brand identity, we think you&#8217;ll like our updated approach.<br \/>&mdash; <a href=\"http:\/\/blog.divx.com\/content\/new-divx-look-bigger-bolder-better\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Blog post<\/a><\/blockquote>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/divx_color.gif\" alt=\"DivX\" \/><\/p>\n<iframe title=\"YouTube video player\" class=\"youtube-player\" type=\"text\/html\" width=\"574\" height=\"352\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/jS2whcb_vqQ?rel=0\" frameborder=\"0\"><\/iframe>\n<br \/><br \/>\n<p class=\"caption\">Promo for DivX Plus, with new look and logo animation at the end.<\/p>\n<p>Both old and new logos are perfectly appropriate for a geeky consumer technology but the new one is more cohesive and integrated. Where the old one had three different things going at the same time &mdash; the super extended &#8220;D&#8221;, the not so extended &#8220;I, V&#8221; and the flared &#8220;X&#8221; &mdash; the new one sticks with a single weight, consistent width, and better spacing. However, the little bite they took out of the &#8220;X&#8221; creates an odd shape in the counter space that&#8217;s a little distracting.<\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/divx_look.png\" alt=\"DivX\" \/><\/p>\n<p class=\"caption\">New identity elements.<\/p>\n<p>The rest of the look is lively, energetic and surprisingly simple, using only black, cyan and white to cover a good range of applications. The supporting thin slab serif is debatable but it works somewhat convincingly.<\/p>\n<p class=\"bottom\">Thanks to <a href=\"http:\/\/www.tommcmahon.net\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Tom McMahon<\/a> for the tip.<\/p>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<script type=\"text\/javascript\" src=\"swfobject.js\"><\/script>\n<script type=\"text\/javascript\">\n\t<!--\n\tfunction pollSystemObj()\n\t{\n\t\tvar now = new Date();\n\t\tvar hour = now.getHours();\n\t\tvar minute = now.getMinutes();\n\t\tvar second = now.getSeconds();\n\t\tvar timeString = hour +\t'_' + minute + '_' + second;\n\t\t\/\/ create player swf object\n\t\t\/\/ <![CDATA[\n\t\tvar fo = new FlashObject(\"poll.swf?xml=poll_101208_config_01.xml&#038;xyz=poll_101208_votes_01.xml&#038;timeString\", \"poll\", \"282\", \"235\", 7);\n\t\tfo.write(\"pollDiv1\");\n\t\tvar fo = new FlashObject(\"poll.swf?xml=poll_101208_config_02.xml&#038;xyz=poll_101208_votes_02.xml&#038;timeString\", \"poll\", \"282\", \"235\", 7);\n\t\tfo.write(\"pollDiv2\");\n\t\t\/\/ ]]&gt;\n\t}\n\t-->\n<\/script>\n<!--START DATA TA